===Etymology 1===
{{etymid|ja|kan}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=o|かん}}

{{IPAfont|/kwan/}} → {{IPAfont|/kan/}}

From {{der|ja|ltc|sort=かん|管|tr=kuɑn<sup>X</sup>||pipe, tube}}.<ref name="KDJc">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten Concise}}</ref>

The {{m|en|pipe}} sense is traced back to the writings of {{w|Zhuangzi}}, already an influential text in Japan in the 700s.<ref name="KDJc"/>

The {{m|en|[[brush]] [[handle]]}} sense is traced back to the text of the {{m|ja|詩経|tr=Shikyō||{{w|Classic of Poetry}}}}, an Old Chinese poetry anthology written from the 11th to 7th centuries BCE and already influencing Japanese writing since the mid-700s.<ref name="KDJc"/>

The {{m|en|wind instrument}} sense is sourced from the {{m|ja|延喜式|tr={{w|Engishiki}}}} of 927.<ref name="KDJ"/>

